Exercise 13.24: What would happen if the version of HasPtr in this section
didn’t define a destructor? What if HasPtr didn’t define the copy
constructor?

Answer:
We would have a memory leak for each occurrence since the synthesized destructor would not delete ps itself but only the pointer.

If HasPtr didn't define the copy constructor then the synthesized copy constructor would be called and it will only copy
the pointer to ps but not the string itself.